CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  0http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csNo symptoms

No symptoms at all.

  1http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csNo significant disability

Despite symptoms; able to carry out all usual duties and activities.

  2http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csSlight disability

Unable to carry out all previous activities, but able to look after own affairs without assistance.

  3http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csModerate disability

Requiring some help, but able to walk without assistance.

  4http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csModerately severe disability

Unable to walk without assistance and unable to attend to own bodily needs without assistance.

  5http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csSevere disability

Bedridden, incontinent and requiring constant nursing care and attention.

  6http://testSK.org/CodeSystem/mrs-score-csDead

Patient deceased.

Expansion performed internally based on codesystem Stroke Procedure Not Done Reason Code System v0.1.0 (CodeSystem)

This value set contains 11 concepts

CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  time-windowhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csOutside Therapeutic Window

Patient presented or evaluated outside the established time limit for the procedure.

  no-lvohttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csNo Large Vessel Occlusion (LVO)

An eligible large vessel occlusion for thrombectomy was not identified.

  contraindicationhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csContraindication Present

A medical contraindication to the procedure existed (e.g., bleeding risk).

  patient-refusalhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csPatient/Family Refusal

The patient or their legal representative refused the procedure.

  transferhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csTransferred to Another Facility

The patient was transferred to another hospital for the procedure.

  unavailablehttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csProcedure Unavailable

The procedure was not available at the facility (e.g., lack of equipment, staff).

  disabilityhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csSevere Preexisting Disability

Patient's baseline disability made benefit from the procedure unlikely.

  mild-strokehttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csMild Stroke / Rapid Improvement

Stroke symptoms were too mild or improved rapidly, not justifying the procedure risk.

  done-elsewherehttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csPerformed Elsewhere

The procedure had already been performed at another facility prior to arrival/transfer.

  costhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csCost / No Insurance

Financial or coverage reasons prevented the procedure.

  unknownhttp://testSK.org/CodeSystem/stroke-proc-not-done-reason-csReason Unknown

The reason was not documented or is unknown.
